Three avalanches hit the village of Galtuer in Tirol, western Austria, within two days.
To date, more than 18 people have been killed, more than 10 injured and 21 are still missing, Austrian television reported Wednesday night.
In Austria, the latest torrent of snow -- three stories high and 600 feet wide -- smashed into the town of Valzur, where two people were killed.
The Austrian army said five people were missing.
